						October 17, 2013 5:40 pm					</div>
										<p>Nice article. Confession. Rarely will I buy music. Spotify rocks. But I find myself giving more and more money to street performers. Not because I feel compelled to bankroll them for supporting services that directly or indirectly hurt their profits, but because in the moments I experience their music, I appreciate their contribution to my city. The expectation to make money through one&#8217;s art is one I think all artists need to rid themselves from. However, I do see my giving a dollar or two simply a way to acknowledge the roll music plays in enhancing our communities. I support that.  As music gets more and more digital, it&#8217;s harder to make that connection.</p>
