					<div class="c-date">
						October 18, 2013 5:49 pm					</div>
										<p>You make a lot of good points, and it does come down to those who enjoy someone&#8217;s creative output being willing to pay toward&#8217;s supporting the creator.  There seems to be an almost innate joy stimulated in people when they get something of worth for free, and that&#8217;s hard to overcome without some sort of reminder that things need to be paid for.  Human nature does not seem to tend towards, &#8220;Great song, here&#8217;s a buck.&#8221;  Your point that we all need to do a better job of appreciating artists by paying for their work hits the nail on the head.</p>
